# M5 P07 — Capture-the-flag end-to-end on the code-built Crossfire map.
#
# Verifies the visible CTF behaviors:
#   1. Flags render at their team bases (HOME state) on round start.
#   2. Pickup transition: the player walks into the BLUE flag, flag
#      transitions to CARRIED, attached to the player's chest.
#   3. Capture transition: the player (RED) carrying BLUE flag touches
#      the RED home flag → both flags HOME, team_score += 5.
#   4. Drop on death: a fresh-armed carry, kill the carrier (deadly
#      tile / shot), flag transitions to DROPPED.
#
# To skip walking the entire 4480-px arena, we use the `flag_carry`
# debug directive to pre-arm the carrier state and `spawn_at` to drop
# the player near the home flag for capture verification.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/m5_ctf_capture
seed 1 2

# Code-built CTF map. mode_mask=FFA|TDM|CTF, 2 flags, per-team spawns.
map crossfire
mode ctf

# Park the player just east of the RED home flag so we can verify
# (a) at-base render (tick 0) and (b) capture from a few px walk.
# Crossfire RED flag: x = 320, platform top y ≈ 1016.
spawn_at 380 970

# Default aim is "200 px to the right of chest" — fine for face direction.
contact_sheet ctf_capture cols 4 cell 320 180

at 1   shot t1_round_start_red_at_home
at 30  shot t30_player_at_red_base

# Arm the carrier state: local mech is now carrying flag idx 1 (BLUE).
# This bypasses the long traversal across the map and lets us verify
# the carry visual + capture transition.
at 40 flag_carry 1
at 50 shot t50_carrying_blue_flag

# Walk LEFT into the RED home flag (~60 px away). RUN_SPEED ≈ 4.6 px/tick.
at 60 press left
at 95 release left
at 95 shot t95_capture_landed

# After capture both flags are HOME and the team score is 5.
at 120 shot t120_post_capture_home

at 130 end
